OL,6,F"Then I had the neighbour at the
OL,7,Fbottom of the garden ringing me saying
OL,8,Fyour house is on fire.
OL,10,F"I had another neighbour very quickly
OL,11,Fsaying, you know, your house is on
OL,12,Ffire. So, the neighbours had picked up
OL,13,Fon it as well.
OL,15,F"I went to bed and forgot all about
OL,16,Fit. Normally I do a house check.
OL,17,FThat's off, that's off and you think
OL,18,Fyou're all safe."
OL,20,F"I'm very lucky to get out alive. It
OL,21,Fcould have been so easily avoided. "
